<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here are three stylized facts about accounting=
:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you are a junior or mid-level acco=
untant at a big public accounting firm, you probably know a lot about accou=
nting. Your accounting training is reasonably fresh in your mind, and you a=
re applying it all day in your job as an accountant.</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">If you are a quite senior accountant at a big public acc=
ounting firm, you might know=C2=A0<em>ever so slightly less=C2=A0</em>accou=
nting? Your accounting training occurred a long time ago. Your day job invo=
lves a lot of managing people, schmoozing clients and setting firm strategy=
;=C2=A0you probably spend less time in the details of technical accounting =
questions than you used to. You didn=E2=80=99t get to where you are today=
=C2=A0<em>exclusively=C2=A0</em>by being good at accounting, though that pr=
obably helped; you owe your promotions to some other, less accounting-relat=
ed skills.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Accountants are subject=
 to continuing-education requirements, where professional bodies, regulator=
s and their firms require them to periodically take classes on accounting a=
nd pass exams to make sure they still know accounting stuff.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When you combine those stylized facts, you get=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35003841.257348/a=
HR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMucGNhb2J1cy5vcmcvcGNhb2ItZGV2L2RvY3MvZGVmYXVsdC1zb3VyY2Uv=
ZW5mb3JjZW1lbnQvZGVjaXNpb25zL2RvY3VtZW50cy8xMDUtMjAyNC0wMjIta3BtZy1uZXRoZXJ=
sYW5kcy5wZGY_c2Z2cnNuPWNlNDZjMjExXzI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa3219d76" ite=
mprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"colo=
r: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bor=
der-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #c=
cc;">stories like this</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">From 2012 to 2015, and again from January 2020=
 to July 2023, [Marc] Hogeboom served on KPMG Netherlands=E2=80=99 Manageme=
nt Board. ...</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2018, Hogeboom solicited subordinates in th=
e Firm to assist him with passing a test in connection with mandatory train=
ing for audit=C2=A0 supervisors. Eventually, a subordinate on one of his au=
dit engagement teams agreed to sit with him and assist while he took the on=
line test. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2020, while serving as the Head of Assuranc=
e, on the Firm=E2=80=99s Management Board, and in its Regulatory Office Cor=
e Team, Hogeboom prevailed upon several subordinate members of his engageme=
nt team to share test answers with him by accompanying him while he took on=
line training tests.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Yesterday the US Public Company Accounting Ove=
rsight Board, which regulates US accountants, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.=
bloombergbusiness.com/click/35003841.257348/aHR0cHM6Ly9wY2FvYnVzLm9yZy9uZXd=
zLWV2ZW50cy9uZXdzLXJlbGVhc2VzL25ld3MtcmVsZWFzZS1kZXRhaWwvcGNhb2ItaW1wb3Nlcy=
1yZWNvcmQtLTI1LW1pbGxpb24tZmluZS1vbi1rcG1nLW5ldGhlcmxhbmRzLWFuZC1iYXJzLWEtZ=
mlybS1sZWFkZXItYWZ0ZXItZXhhbS1jaGVhdGluZy0tbWlzaW5mb3JtaW5nLWludmVzdGlnYXRv=
cnM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB797b485e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">fined the Dutch unit of the =
global accounting firm KPMG NV</a> $25 million because =E2=80=9Cwidespread =
improper answer sharing occurred at the firm over a five-year period and th=
at the firm made multiple misrepresentations to the PCAOB about its knowled=
ge of the misconduct.=E2=80=9D<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote=
-4" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-botto=
m-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !impo=
rtant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a> KPMG Netherlands employees had to take lots of internal training cours=
es, some of the courses had tests that they had to pass, a lot of it was on=
line, and apparently nobody took the tests that seriously so they regularly=
 shared answers with each other:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">From at least October 2017 through=
 2022, hundreds of KPMG Netherlands personnel, including partners, were inv=
olved in improper answer sharing related to training tests, and in some cas=
es the NBA Knowledge tests. This misconduct occurred primarily through emai=
ls attaching documents or images containing the contents of the tests and/o=
r answers to test questions. KPMG Netherlands personnel also jointly took t=
ests that were intended to assess individual knowledge.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Some of this was peer employees sharing the an=
swers with each other, but some of it was the bosses specifically demanding=
 that their underlings help them take the tests. Makes sense! The bosses ar=
e good at managing people; the underlings are good at accounting.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are lots of=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35003841.257348/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZ=
XJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDYtMjgvZG9uLXQtY2hlYXQtb24tdGhlLWV0=
aGljcy1leGFtP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MTEyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXR=
tX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQxMSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdH=
VmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBa72bbf41" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D=
"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: non=
e !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; borde=
r-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">cases like this</a>; KPMG i=
tself <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35003841.257=
348/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMucGNhb2J1cy5vcmcvcGNhb2ItZGV2L2RvY3MvZGVmYXVsdC1zb3V=
yY2UvZW5mb3JjZW1lbnQvZGVjaXNpb25zL2RvY3VtZW50cy8xMDUtMjAyMi0wMzIta3BtZy11ay=
5wZGY_c2Z2cnNuPWU5NDFmYmFiXzQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1d1f2bfb" itemprop=
=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0=
00000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-b=
ottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">=
had another one</a> in 2022. Cheating on internal exams is for the PCAOB a =
little like <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/350038=
41.257348/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtM=
DItMDIvdGhlLXNlYy13YW50cy10by1zZWUtbW9yZS1waG9uZXM_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQxMTI0X01P=
TkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm0=
9MjQwNDExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB889e6d2d=
" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D=
"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px=
; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-colo=
r: #ccc;">
improper cell-phone use</a> for the US Securities and Exchange Commission. =
It=E2=80=99s a perpetual cash cow =E2=80=94=C2=A0every bank has people who =
did business on personal cell phones, every accounting firm apparently has =
people who cheated on training exams =E2=80=94=C2=A0and, while it isn=E2=80=
=99t particularly bad in itself, perhaps it is a sign of bigger problems. F=
or one thing, it is bad if accountants are unethical and cheat on exams. Fo=
r another thing, it=E2=80=99s bad if they can=E2=80=99t pass the exams with=
out cheating! They=E2=80=99re supposed to know accounting.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But you don=E2=80=99t want to overstate that. =
The problem here does not seem to be that they didn=E2=80=99t know accounti=
ng. The problem is that they didn=E2=80=99t take the trainings or exams ser=
iously; they did not see the trainings as essential to their work as accoun=
tants, but as meaningless administrative box-checking to be done as quickly=
 as possible before they got back to their actual jobs. Actually sometimes =
they were in such a hurry to get back to their actual jobs that they left e=
arly and made someone else finish checking the boxes:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In 2021, another senior leader at =
the Firm, the Supervisory Chairman, engaged in improper answer sharing. =E2=
=80=A6 Shortly after joining the=C2=A0 Supervisory Board, the Supervisory C=
hairman received assistance from a staff member while taking two mandatory =
trainings that the Supervisory Board had assigned to the Supervisory Chairm=
an. The staff member sat next to the Supervisory Chairman while he took the=
 two training tests, and the staff member finished one of the tests for the=
 Supervisory Chairman when he left for a meeting before completing the test=
.=C2=A0</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I guess if your boss tells you to finish his m=
andatory training exam for him, you have to do it? Does seem like a problem=
 though.</p>
<table class=3D"header" width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" cellp=
adding=3D"0">
<tr>
<td class=3D"body-header-container" style=3D"border-collapse: collapse; mso=
-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt;">
<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Change of control</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Many companies have debt agreements that inclu=
de a =E2=80=9Cchange of control put.=E2=80=9D If the company has a change o=
f control, the creditors can demand their money back immediately, often at =
a premium. This can be a big deal. If a company has bonds outstanding that =
are due in 2030 and trade at 80 cents on the dollar, and then it has a chan=
ge of control, it might have to buy the bonds back immediately at 101. It w=
ill need to come up with a lot of money, probably by borrowing it at more e=
xpensive rates.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The intuition here is that, often, when a comp=
any is taken over, its debt becomes riskier: If you are a bondholder of som=
e reasonably stable public company, and then it gets bought in a leveraged =
buyout and loaded up with more debt, you will be sad; your debt will lose v=
alue. The deal that you originally struck with the company has changed, and=
 you=E2=80=99ll want to get out.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">What is a change of control? There are lots of=
 ways for a company to change hands, some of which are bad for creditors an=
d some of which aren=E2=80=99t. The rough idea is that if the company is ac=
quired for cash, that=E2=80=99s probably bad. So an all-cash merger is norm=
ally a change of control, or a sale of =E2=80=9Call or substantially all=E2=
=80=9D of the assets,=C2=A0or someone (a person or firm) acquiring a majori=
ty of the stock. Whereas an all-stock merger with another public company is=
 less likely to hurt the credit, and so normally does not trigger a change =
of control put.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"co=
lor: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; b=
order-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgrou=
nd-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Here=E2=80=99s a weird one, though: Arguably=
=C2=A0<em>losing a proxy fight=C2=A0</em>is a change of control. If an acti=
vist buys stock in a public company and agitates for change, or a hostile b=
idder proposes a takeover, and the company rejects the proposal, so the act=
ivist/bidder launches a proxy fight to get her own candidates on the board =
of directors, and the company fights back, and the activist/bidder=C2=A0win=
s and gets a majority of directors, then:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">In some real sense, the activist or h=
ostile bidder has taken control of the company: Her allies now control the =
board and can change the company=E2=80=99s policies or approve a sale.</li>=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">That is, in expectation, bad for credi=
tors: The activist will typically want the company to be more levered and r=
iskier than the incumbent board did, and the hostile bidder will probably a=
cquire the company in a way that is bad for its debt.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so it is common for debt agreements to hav=
e a change of control put for losing a proxy fight. Technically the way thi=
s is written is that it is a change of control for a majority of the compan=
y=E2=80=99s board of directors to not be =E2=80=9Ccontinuing directors,=E2=
=80=9D where a continuing director is either (1) a director who is in place=
 at the time of the debt deal or (2) a new director who was approved by a m=
ajority of the previous continuing directors. So the board can amicably rep=
lace itself over time, but if it is replaced all at once by a hostile slate=
, that=E2=80=99s a change of control.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This strikes me as a basically correct intuiti=
on about creditors=E2=80=99 interests, but it causes a problem. The problem=
 is that management can use the change of control put as a weapon in the pr=
oxy fight.=C2=A0It can say: =E2=80=9CLook, we have all this debt outstandin=
g, and we are not in the best financial shape. (Thus the proxy fight!) If w=
e lose this proxy fight, the debt will all come due immediately at 101 cent=
s on the dollar. We won=E2=80=99t be able to refinance all that debt immedi=
ately, and so losing the proxy fight will cause the company to go bankrupt.=
 So vote for us!=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That is a bit harsh, to tell shareholders that=
 they=C2=A0<em>can=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>vote for an alternative board of dir=
ectors because that would bankrupt the company. It is not a good look for t=
he incumbent directors to threaten to blow up the company unless they keep =
their jobs. There is a solution, though it is a bit of a silly one: The inc=
umbent board can just =E2=80=9Capprove=E2=80=9D the activist=E2=80=99s cand=
idates, for purposes of the change of control put. This way, if the company=
 loses the proxy fight, the activist=E2=80=99s directors are still =E2=80=
=9Ccontinuing directors=E2=80=9D and the change of control put isn=E2=80=99=
t triggered. Of course, the provision is there in the first place because c=
reditors really=C2=A0<em>don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>want the company to lose a=
 proxy fight. But somebody=E2=80=99s interests will suffer, and if the boar=
d can help shareholders while being a bit rude to creditors it probably sho=
uld.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Jef Feeley and Mike=
 Leonard <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35003841.=
257348/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDQtMDkv=
bWFjeS1zLXN1ZWQtZm9yLXNpZ25hbGluZy1kZWJ0LXBheW1lbnQtc3BlZWQtdXAtaW4tcHJveHk=
tZmlnaHQ_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQxMTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc2=
91cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNDExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf042c0d0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">reported Tuesday</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Macy=E2=80=99s Inc. has =E2=80=9Cweaponized=E2=
=80=9D its debt agreements as part of a proxy fight with a pair of investme=
nt firms, putting its financial future at risk, a pension fund claimed in s=
uing the retailer.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The takeover defense, which Macy=E2=80=99s is =
threatening to deploy in a fight with Arkhouse Management and Brigade Capit=
al Management, would accelerate the payment of more than $1.5 billion in de=
bt and burden the company=E2=80=99s finances, according to the lawsuit.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">From=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/35003841.257348/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC5pby9kb2N1bW=
VudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3J5aGtKY1pEQU1ody92MA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cBa4d192f9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;">the complaint</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If half of the Board is replaced in a proxy co=
ntest, that would constitute a Change of Control under the terms of the Rel=
evant Notes unless the incumbent Board simply =E2=80=9Capproves=E2=80=9D th=
e dissident nominees. The incumbent directors can approve dissident directo=
r nominees for the limited purpose of disabling debt acceleration while sim=
ultaneously recommending that stockholders vote to elect the incumbent cand=
idates over the dissident candidates. Moreover, under well-established Dela=
ware law, the incumbent directors have a duty to approve dissident nominees=
 unless they have a good faith belief that the dissidents are known looters=
 or would implement a business program that would cause the Company to be u=
nable to meet its legal obligations to creditors.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If the Company were forced repurchase the Rele=
vant Notes at 101% of their principal, it could be devastating to Macy=E2=
=80=99s financial health. Overall, the Company has $1.059 billion outstandi=
ng under the Relevant Notes and only $1.034 billion in cash and cash equiva=
lents as of February 3, 2024.=C2=A0 =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Moreover, the Federal Reserve=E2=80=99s curren=
t federal funds target interest rate is 5.25% to 5.5%, which means if Macy=
=E2=80=99s was forced to refinance the Relevant Notes in the near future, i=
t would have to pay significantly higher interest rates.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Therefore, a loyal board acting in the best in=
terests of the Company and not motivated by a desire to perpetuate its term=
 in office would do everything in its power to avoid triggering the Change =
of Control provisions in the Relevant Notes in connection with a contested =
director election unless the dissident candidates were criminals or known l=
ooters.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Arkhouse and Brigade don=E2=80=99t seem like =
=E2=80=9Cknown looters,=E2=80=9D and in fact this thing seems to be going t=
he way hostile takeover fights normally go, with a grudging transition to f=
riendliness. Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Crystal Tse <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/35003841.257348/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNv=
bS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDQtMTAvbWFjeS1zLWFkZHMtdHdvLWFya2hvdXNlLW5vbWl=
uZWVzLXRvLWJvYXJkLWRlYWwtdGFsa3MtY29udGludWUtbHV0dWNxMms_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDQxMT=
I0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX=
3Rlcm09MjQwNDExJnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5e=
07b572" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" st=
yle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-widt=
h: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgroun=
d-color: #ccc;">reported yesterday</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Macy=E2=80=99s Inc. named two new directors no=
minated by activist investor Arkhouse Management Co., which agreed to end i=
ts effort to seek majority board representation as it attempts to acquire t=
he department-store operator.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Richard Clark and Richard Markee will join the=
 board and its finance committee that oversees acquisition proposals, accor=
ding to a statement from the retailer Wednesday. Macy=E2=80=99s is =E2=80=
=9Ccontinuing to engage=E2=80=9D with Arkhouse and Brigade Capital Manageme=
nt on their proposal to acquire the company, the company said.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><em>Settling=C2=A0</em>a proxy fight doesn=E2=
=80=99t trigger the puts. Of course presumably if Arkhouse and Brigade=C2=
=A0<em>acquire the company</em>, that <em>will </em>be a change of control.=
 But that will be their problem, not the shareholders=E2=80=99.</p>
